\frac{x^2}{a^2}+\frac{y^2}{b^2}=1
\frac{x^2+y^2}{F(\phi)^2}=1,
F(\phi)=\frac{ab}{\sqrt{(b\cos\phi)^2+(a\sin\phi)^2}}
\phi=\phi(x,y)=\arctan(\frac{y}{x}).
x=r\cos\phi
y=r\sin\phi
a^2b^2
r
a
b
r\ge 0
\frac{r^2\cos^2\phi}{a^2}+\frac{r^2\sin^2\phi}{b^2}=1.
r^2\left(b^2\cos^2\phi+a^2\sin^2\phi\right)=a^2b^2.
r=\frac{ab}{\sqrt{b^2\cos^2\phi+a^2\sin^2\phi}}.
